    "extras": [
      "Book Alfa Pendular and Intercidades tickets early on CP for the best promo fares; last-minute long-distance rail can cost nearly double.",
      "Lisbon and Sintra monument slots sell out first for 10am-1pm entries, so reserve Pena Palace, Jerónimos, and Belém Tower before you fly.",
      "Portugal is very card-friendly, but keep a little cash for pastry shops, beach kiosks, and smaller Alentejo taverns.",
      "Pack a light jacket even in shoulder season — Porto evenings and Sintra mornings can feel cool and windy.",
      "Tap water is safe everywhere, and many cities have refill points, so a reusable bottle saves money during long walking days.",
      "Portugal is in the Schengen zone; Indian passport holders should budget roughly ₹8,500–₹9,000 for the visa and apply at least a month ahead."
    ],
